# public-surface-forbidden.regex
#
# Patterns that MUST NOT appear in any artifact published to an external
# registry (npm / PyPI / Docker Hub / public web). Per the Public Surface
# Hygiene Mandate — canonical text lives in the consumer's ecosystem
# CLAUDE.md; this file is the machine-readable contract surface.
#
# Format: one extended-regex pattern per non-empty, non-comment line.
# Lines starting with `#` are comments. Patterns are passed to `grep -E`
# with word boundaries when applicable; treat each line as a standalone
# `grep -E -n` invocation.
#
# Consumers extend this set by sourcing it from their own
# `<consumer>/dev-tools/public-surface-forbidden.regex` and concatenating
# project-specific task-prefix patterns. Do not edit this file with
# consumer-specific prefixes — keep the contract surface neutral.

# Internal SDLC artefact references (PRD / creative / plans / insights /
# reflection). Closed pattern set — every consumer's task IDs route through
# one of these.
\bPRD-[A-Z]{2,10}-[0-9]{4}\b
\bcreative-[A-Z]{2,10}-[0-9]{4}\b
\bplans-[A-Z]{2,10}-[0-9]{4}\b
\binsights-[A-Z]{2,10}-[0-9]{4}\b
\breflection-[A-Z]{2,10}-[0-9]{4}\b

# Internal-only repo paths inside the canonical Datarim layout. Public
# packages must not link to these — they are gitignored in the framework
# repo and the link target returns 404 anyway.
\bdatarim/(tasks|creative|plans|insights|reflection)/

# Milestone-code references that leak phase / iteration internals. Use
# version numbers in public copy instead.
\b(?:M|Phase) ?[1-9][0-9]*\b
